The paper deals with the problem of compressed sensing, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The focus is on recovering a spectrally sparse signal, which involves the use of structured matrices and low-rank matrix completion techniques, which are also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the use of convex relaxation, which is a common technique in optimization and signal processing (cs.SI).
